> That was not a Beetle engine but a jointly developed Engine by Porsche and
> VW called the Type 4 Engine, When the water jacket was put on it
> became the WASSERBOXER.

Actually the wasserboxer has less in common with the type 4 engine than with
the original Beetle (type 1) engine, with which which it shares a multitude
of parts.  Not that the wasserboxer is exactly the same as either, but it
has more in common with the type 1 engine  than the type 4 engine.

